OL,3,GSouth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FStrong winds on Wednesday with
OL,6,Fgales possible near exposed coasts and
OL,7,Fhills. Sunshine turning hazier through
OL,8,Fthe day as cloud builds, with a chance
OL,9,Fof showers in the far west.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA mostly clear night to come
OL,12,Fwith higher cloud moving into the west
OL,13,Fof the region. Staying dry, buts gusty
OL,14,Fwinds remain along coasts and high
OL,15,Fground.
OL,16,
OL,17,CThursday:FAnother bright and sunny day
OL,18,Fwill follow for all, albeit hazy for
OL,19,Fmany, especially in the west. Remains
OL,20,Fgusty across the high ground of Devon
OL,21,Fand Cornwall.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
